<TITLE> 6 in remand for Balaka sculpture attack </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Dec. 4 (bdnews24.com)  Six Ulama Anjumane Al Bayenat activists, who were arrested while vandalising the 'Balaka' sculpture in Motijheel, were sent into two-day remand on Thursday. Metropolitan judge AKM Emdadul granted the remand plea of investigation officer SI Jamal Uddin. The accused are Mostaq Ahmed Chowdhury, Arafat Hossain, Ziaur Rahman, Hasibul Islam, Abdul Bari Sheikh and Jahangir Hossain. Over 100 activists attacked the sculpture on the night of Nov 30, claiming it was "un-Islamic". The vandals later retreated in the face of police who filed a case with Motijheel police station. bdnews24
